name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
You don’t get to decide if you caused harm to someone. 

Intent is totally irrelevant if harm is caused. Intent doesn’t change a thing. 

I don’t even feel safe asking for an apology from friends when they harm me. 

I always feel shame and guilt for being harmed. It’s not right.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
It’s too many now to remember all of them, and all the incidents. Damage is done. 

My lived experience of this journey is always always disrespected and ignored. Always. 

Every single day. 

Barely anyone is accountable for harm they do to me. They probably don’t even care.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
So many people I love have caused me deep harm and I’ve never told them because I’m afraid to lose all my friends. 

How is me feeling like this in any way “progressive”?  

I’m tired of being polite. 

Lots of people owe me apologies I’ve never had. But as always I just take it.

If we’re constantly living in reactivity we’ll end up consumed by anger. 

I have value. I’m loved. I have friends who tell me tough truths I need to hear. 

All I need.

tweet:
I hope it’s OK to share my feelings without it be personal. 

I’m just a little triggered and hurt. 

I have no malice towards anyone. I love people in so many different communities with different stories and they are all good, loving people. 

I just had to say something.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
I have my people. They all know who they are. You probably do. 

Some have been on my podcast or will be soon. Most of them don’t use labels.  

Even the deconstruction spaces, most people are good, kind, loving people. But I guess I wanted more.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single

tweet:
It feels personal. I’ll be honest I wonder if some ableist people think I’m mentally unstable or some rubbish like that, just because I’m vulnerable. 

I feel left out of a clique, and this time it’s by people who’ve not been doing this as long.

It’s painful.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
I have to say this or I’ll explode. 

It hurts to feel like my story isn’t as valuable & I’m not as respected as others, not invited/wanted in parts the deconstruction community. 

I’ve been living deconstruction for 10-15 years. Now everyone is doing it, and leaving me out.

Example: flirting.

However, I’m aware of all of this now and this means I can actively work on it.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
Therapy for me is unlearning all these patterns and routines and safe but ultimately painful ways of seeing the world. 

It has to be autism informed and trauma informed therapy to understand how my brain operates and how I can heal in a healthy way. 

My therapist is autistic.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
Circumstances and trauma have conditioned my autistic brain to expect rejection and “betrayal” (things being done or said behind my back between friends). 

In the past I may have even self-sabotaged relationships just to feel “safe” when I am rejected.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
When I go to the office my body feels tense and unsafe from the moment I leave the house till the moment I am settled at my desk. 

Any time in any kind of community my body is ready and waiting for any kind of rejection and social exclusion  of any kind.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
Realising just how much I struggle with any sort of community and being out in the world. 

Part of this is trauma based, part RSD, part autism. Unless I’m in a space when in my head I feel in control / safe, my body will feel tension and discomfort.

I want to differentiate here form OCD. 

OCD is about obsessions and compulsions and having to perform things in a strict order. There are intrusive thoughts and obsessions. 

Autism is more just the lens you view the world. The way your brain encounters it.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single

Also “doing the right thing” can mean: 

- doing the right thing legally, morally and ethically 
- following all the steps in a step by step process or instruction
- following correct procedure 
- following social rules or unspoken rules I have had to learn 
- following any rules

“You were traumatised so you should get compensated by the universe.” 

He sees others with similar lived experiences having these things I desire and gets upset I haven’t got those “compensations” of trauma as that’s a “rule”.

No wonder I get so down.

tweet:
My brain thinks if I do “the right thing” then I get positive outcomes automatically. That’s “the rules”

So when this rule is “broken” then I end up angry and in a depressive spiral. Wanting to change the rule to “nothing you do matters” as it’s less painful. 

Autism huh?

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦

tweet:
Another autism “moment of clarity”: 

My brain thinks if you follow certain rules there are automatically certain outcomes.  

If these outcomes don’t happen my brain gets freaked out & goes into a spiral/meltdown. 

Trauma messes with what are reasonable rules & outcomes.

This may represent my best self in some ways but not necessarily what I am thinking or feeling at that moment.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦

tweet:
I often have to observe conversations I am in to pick up tone and what is OK to talk about and what will be funny and decide how to interact with it. 

I also often don’t pick up social cues with new people especially and have had to train myself to actively learn them.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦

We’ve been brainwashed, indoctrinated into thinking this is the only way to live or that it’s normal and we just have to accept it. 

Well we don’t. 

I don’t know the answer, I wish I did. But it can’t go on. 

This system is killing us and it’s killing our planet too.

The common denominator: capitalism. 

This system treats us like machines and exploits us. And it’s racist too. 

This is not how humans were meant to live.

Just to help NT people in any form of relationship with #ActuallyAutistic people. 

Know we are often afraid to ask for clarification on things. 

So explaining things simply and clearly really helps us. And although it’s tempting, be careful not to use a patronising tone.

tweet:

It’s NT’s job to educate themselves and listen and understand us. 

Being #ActuallyAustistic does not make us deficient, we are not deficient.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
This is why I have dismissed any evidence to the contrary so easily.  

My autistic brain thinks this isn’t correct or doesn’t fit with structures he knows so dismisses it.

Therapy for me will be unlearning these structures and finding new ones.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
This wasn’t like an emotional decision. 

My brain knew no different so objectively decided, this is how things work, and just accepted it. 

And parts of my brain still think these are the rules, so still try to follow them or even enforce them.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
Realised in therapy how my autistic brain observed and accepted the rules of the universe due to trauma:

- I don’t matter as much as others  
- I will always be excluded 
- I am powerless over my life 
- People you love abandon you 
- I am not allowed good things

tweet:
These labels, “deconstruction”, “exvangelical” can be useful in the right context and I love people who use them. 

But they can easily become new cliques with gatekeepers and rules.

I don’t use them in relation to me for this reason. I’m me, on a personal journey of awakening.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:

It’s about how we see the world, how we interact with it, how we do community, how we believe.

In / out, exclusive, cliquey thinking and behaviour isn’t growth, it’s the same shit, with different language. 

Honestly, stop it. https://t.co/bOIGZoH8AD

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
I do my best to ignore the signs. I have a graphic I use to remind me. 

But it’s a daily battle. I have to keep convincing myself and exercise self-control to stop myself spiralling.

You probably know more people with this than you realise. 

So it’s worth being educated.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
And then what happens is you end up self-sabotaging friendships and relationships. Either trying to over compensate or just pushing them away before they get a chance to hurt you. 

Which makes it a self-fulfilling prophecy & makes it worse.  

I’d give anything not to have this.

description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single

If you see people you love applying even the remotest different standards to others in your friendship group your brain becomes paranoid. 

Basically any reason the brain can find that someone is rejecting you, they use to convince you.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦
description: Host @poemapodcast & @kalelleiakevin • Author • ‘Talented conversationalist' - @mikemchargue • 4w5 • #ActuallyAutistic HSP ADHD RSD • He/Him • Demi Het • Single
tweet:
Imagine your brain sending messages to you when friends go silent or disappear or don’t reply or exclude you from even the smallest thing they are all doing (even by accident), that these people secretly hate you / laugh at you. 

And even if you know it’s not true you feel it.

name: James Prescott’s Rate Limit Is Exceeded 🇺🇦

Please. It’s as valid as any mental health condition. 

As an extreme sufferer, it will help any kind of relationship I ever have for others to understand this.

I’ve literally had suicidal ideation multiple times due to triggers of RSD. 

I do my best to remind myself not to react in certain ways and remind myself of the truth. But I can’t do it all on my own, none of us with RSD can. 

And it’s even worse when you have autism too.

Please everyone go educate yourself on rejection sensitive dysmorphia. 

Learn about what it can do to people and learn about how people react to certain behaviours. 

It’s really really important. 

I’m tired of constantly educating people on it. 

It’s important to be informed.

But when my mother died this fear was ruptured and questions began, when I read Velvet Elvis, they began to unravel.
